summary: Pokemon of the Week - Mr. Mime
title: Pokemon of the Week - Mr. Mime
description:
Pokemon of the Week - Mr. Mine

Mr. Mime!  Ever since gen 1 I’ve just thought, wow, what a weird pokemon.  I mean, it really looks like a person.  The pokemon that look like people just feel…weird to me.  Like Mr. Mime and Jynx.  That being said, I do find Mime Jr. to be adorable!!  I wouldn’t mind that little one.  I received a Mr. Mime while playing a Wonderlocke team, so I used it there.  Frankly, I was impressed with how well it did work!  It’s definitely not a physically impressive pokemon at all.  But it’s Special moves and strength makes it good at what it does.  And it can put up the walls!

Now, over at serebii.net (follow the link) they’ve reviewed how they think it is best to use it in competitive play.  Despite it’s weaknesses, and how it can be outclassed by other similar pokemon, they did come up with some strategies on how to use it.  I always figure these ideas can at least give you some ideas in using it in a standard play through as well.  Please follow the link to check it out!

summary: i have a question relating to you in the pokemon fandom! is it exclusively the games?
question: i have a question relating to you in the pokemon fandom! is it exclusively the games?
answer:
Probably. :o I haven’t seen an episode of the anime since like. Indigo League got uploaded to Netflix i think alskfdjgsdk

But I’ve also played some of the side games (including but not limited to: Pokemon Battle Revolution, Pokken Tournament, the first two Ranger Games, Pokemon Snap, Pokemon Shuffle, the two PokePark games, Pokemon Rumble, and even the first few minutes of Pokemon Conquest) 

also i’ve attempted to dm a game of Pokemon Tabletop (think like d&d but pokemon)!

body:
Detective Pikachu made me cry.

Not because it was sad or anything.

It was just. So perfect.

The story felt like one of the video games. I felt like I was back at my cousin’s house playing pokemon with them before we all drifted apart.

I felt welcomed.
